The given text is: "DW UHJXODU LQWHUYDOV WKHB DUH HYHU DGGUHVVLQJ WR WKH DPHULFDQ JRYHUQPHQW YDLQ FRPSODLQWV."

Let's try to decrypt this by assuming a shift and checking if the resulting text makes sense. A common approach is to try all possible shifts (1 through 25) and see which one results in a readable message.

I'll write a Python script to try all possible shifts and print the results. This will help us identify the correct shift and the decrypted message.

